The paper proposes a new method for clustering using the k-medoids algorithm, which is a popular algorithm in machine learning and data mining. The paper focuses on the use of pairwise distances between data points and proposes a method to estimate unknown distances using a small subset of the distances. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data mining (cs.DM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB).
